# Mnemosyne Project Rules

## Stack
- Vite 8, vanilla ES modules, no framework
- `qrcode-generator` for QR matrix
- **`@jscad/modeling`** for 3D geometry construction (hull, cuboid, vectorText, extrudeLinear, expand)
- **`@jscad/stl-serializer`** for 3D-printing-ready STL export (always manifold)
- Three.js for interactive 3D viewport (OrbitControls, MeshStandardMaterial, lighting)
- Monad design system via `vendor/monad_system/build/monad.{css,js}` (git submodule)

## Monad design system constraints
- **No `border-radius`** on Atomos components
- **No `box-shadow`** — use layered borders for depth
- **No hardcoded hex** except `#fff` on the QR preview (scanner requires white)
- **No gradients**, no opacity fades — transitions: `var(--threshold-fast)` = 80ms linear
- Always use `--strata-*` tokens for colour/spacing, never raw CSS values
- Available tiers: `monad-*` (layout), `atomos-*` (components), `threshold-*` (nav/transitions)
- `threshold-nav` is `display:none` at ≤1056px — always include a `.threshold-toggle` hamburger in the header so `monad.js` can open it

## Tab switching
- Visibility is controlled with **inline `style.display`**, not the `hidden` attribute
- `id` CSS selectors (specificity 1,0,0) beat `[hidden]` (0,1,0) — `hidden` attribute is silently ignored
- `switchTab(id)` in `app.js` sets `panel.style.display = id === active ? "" : "none"`
- Cross-tab communication uses `CustomEvent` on `document`: `qr-updated` (carries `boolean[][]` matrix or `null`), `tab-changed` (carries tab id string)

## JSCAD geometry / STL rules
- JSCAD is **Z-up**; Three.js is **Y-up**. Convert with: `(x, y, z)_jscad → (x, z, −y)_three` (rotation −90° around X, determinant +1, CCW winding preserved — no need to flip triangle order)
- Build QR modules with `hull(bottomSlab, topSlab)` — two thin `cuboid`s at Z=0 and Z=h — draft angle emerges naturally from the top slab being smaller
- **Never `union()` all modules together for display** — keep them as separate geom3 objects, merge only at the BufferGeometry level by concatenating raw position arrays (`collectPositions` loop)
- For STL: `serialize({ binary: true }, ...jscadParts)` — pass spread array of geom3 objects; returns `[ArrayBuffer, ...]` → `new Blob(rawData, { type: 'model/stl' })`
- Text pipeline: `vectorText → path2.fromPoints → expand (delta≈size*0.07) → extrudeLinear → union` → center → `mirrorX` → `translate` to underside of base plate
- `mirrorX` on back text so it reads correctly when the tag is flipped around its vertical (Y) axis
- `jscadParts` array is the single source of truth for export; `modelGroup` is derived purely for display

## Three.js / canvas rules
- **Give the canvas an explicit CSS `height` (e.g. `height: 460px`)** — never `flex:1` or `min-height` on a canvas whose `height` attribute Three.js is also setting; the attribute leaks into the intrinsic CSS size and causes runaway growth
- `renderer.setSize(w, h, false)` — always pass `false` to avoid Three.js overwriting CSS dimensions
- Read resize dimensions from `canvas.clientWidth / canvas.clientHeight`, NOT from `canvas.parentElement.clientHeight`
- ResizeObserver must observe `canvas` directly (not a parent), with a `requestAnimationFrame` defer and a `lastW/lastH` guard to break the observer→setSize→layout→observer loop
- On tab-show: double-rAF (`rAF(() => rAF(() => ...))`) before resizing + rebuilding, so the browser commits layout first
- Render loop: check `panel.style.display !== "none"` (not `panel.hidden`) to gate rendering
- Use `renderer.setClearColor(new THREE.Color(readCSSVar("--strata-bg")))` instead of `alpha:true` + CSS background — explicit is more reliable

## File layout
- `app.js` — QR generation, tab switching, dispatches `qr-updated`
- `threed.js` — Three.js scene, rebuilds on `qr-updated`, exports STL
- `styles.css` — project styles on top of monad.css
- `index.html` — single page, two `<section>` panels (`#workbench`, `#threed`)
